{"source": "docs", "batch_index": 78, "chunks": [{"chunk_id": "33b7a4991330", "text": "### Don't: Manually construct dicts from typed objects\n\n```jac\n# Bad: Manual dict construction loses type information\nwalker:priv BadCreate {\n    has name: str;\n\n    can create with Root entry {\n        item = here ++> Item(name=self.name);\n        report {\"name\": item.name, \"data\": item.data};  # Don't do this\n    }\n}\n\n# Good: Report the typed object directly\nwalker:priv GoodCreate {\n    has name: str;\n\n    can create with Root entry {\n        item = here ++> Item(name=self.name);\n        report item;  # The runtime handles serialization automatically\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/language/walker-responses.md", "section": "Don't: Manually construct dicts from typed objects", "chunk_id": "33b7a4991330"}}, {"chunk_id": "25ea0b3dfa5a", "text": "The same applies to `def:pub` functions -- return typed objects instead of manually constructed dicts:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/language/walker-responses.md", "section": "Don't: Manually construct dicts from typed objects", "chunk_id": "25ea0b3dfa5a"}}, {"chunk_id": "49d90b070d79", "text": "```jac\n# Bad: Manual dict return\ndef:pub get_task(id: str) -> dict {\n    task = find_task(id);\n    return {\"id\": jid(task), \"title\": task.title, \"done\": task.done};\n}\n\n# Good: Typed return -- client receives a hydrated Task instance\ndef:pub get_task(id: str) -> Task {\n    return find_task(id);\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/language/walker-responses.md", "section": "Don't: Manually construct dicts from typed objects", "chunk_id": "49d90b070d79"}}, {"chunk_id": "776f237a64e4", "text": "### Don't: Report in a loop without accumulation\n\n```jac\nnode Item {\n    has data: str;\n}\n\n# Bad: Creates many small reports\nwalker:priv BadPattern {\n    can process with Item entry {\n        report here.data;  # N reports for N items\n    }\n}\n\n# Good: Accumulate and report once\nwalker:priv GoodPattern {\n    has items: list = [];\n\n    can start with Root entry {\n        visit [-->];\n    }\n\n    can process with Item entry {\n        self.items.append(here.data);\n    }\n\n    can finish with Root exit {\n        report self.items;  # One report with all items\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/language/walker-responses.md", "section": "Don't: Report in a loop without accumulation", "chunk_id": "776f237a64e4"}}, {"chunk_id": "997099069ba8", "text": "### Don't: Assume report order without documentation\n\n```jac\nwalker:priv MyWalker {\n    can work with Root entry {\n        report [\"item1\", \"item2\"];\n        report {\"count\": 2};\n    }\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    result = root spawn MyWalker();\n\n    # Bad: Magic indices\n    data = result.reports[0];\n    meta = result.reports[1];\n\n    # Good: Document or structure clearly\n    # reports[0]: List of items\n    # reports[1]: Metadata object\n    data = result.reports[0] if result.reports else [];\n    meta = result.reports[1] if len(result.reports) > 1 else {};\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/language/walker-responses.md", "section": "Don't: Assume report order without documentation", "chunk_id": "997099069ba8"}}, {"chunk_id": "90b9669dfd5e", "text": "# MCP Server (jac mcp)\n\nThe `jac mcp` server provides a [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) server that gives AI assistants deep knowledge of the Jac language. It exposes grammar specifications, documentation, code examples, compiler tools, and prompt templates through a standardized protocol --so any MCP-compatible AI client can write, validate, format, and debug Jac code.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "MCP Server (jac mcp)", "chunk_id": "90b9669dfd5e"}}, {"chunk_id": "8cf6978d9936", "text": "## Installation\n\nThe MCP server is **built into the `jac` binary** -- there is nothing to install. The protocol (JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio, streamable-HTTP, and SSE) is implemented on the Python standard library, so it pulls in no third-party dependencies. Just run `jac mcp` (see Quick Start below). On older releases it shipped as a separate `jac-mcp` plugin; that package is no longer needed.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "Installation", "chunk_id": "8cf6978d9936"}}, {"chunk_id": "c8bc85400b60", "text": "## Quick Start", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "Quick Start", "chunk_id": "c8bc85400b60"}}, {"chunk_id": "0a41a3813e20", "text": "### 1. Start the MCP server\n\n```bash\njac mcp\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "1. Start the MCP server", "chunk_id": "0a41a3813e20"}}, {"chunk_id": "8a3578d1925a", "text": "This starts the server with the default **stdio** transport, ready for IDE integration.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "1. Start the MCP server", "chunk_id": "8a3578d1925a"}}, {"chunk_id": "cad218c5eb71", "text": "### 2. Inspect what's available\n\n```bash\njac mcp --inspect\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "2. Inspect what's available", "chunk_id": "cad218c5eb71"}}, {"chunk_id": "9f02f7af23dc", "text": "This prints all available resources, tools, and prompts, then exits.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "2. Inspect what's available", "chunk_id": "9f02f7af23dc"}}, {"chunk_id": "301d932f587c", "text": "### 3. Connect your AI client\n\nAdd the server to your AI client's MCP configuration (see [IDE Integration](#ide-integration) below), then start using Jac tools directly from your AI assistant.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "3. Connect your AI client", "chunk_id": "301d932f587c"}}, {"chunk_id": "84e0af361535", "text": "## IDE Integration\n\n<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Claude Desktop</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "84e0af361535"}}, {"chunk_id": "365e83e441fb", "text": "Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or `%APPDATA%\\\\Claude\\\\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows):", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "365e83e441fb"}}, {"chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"jac\": {\n      \"command\": \"jac\",\n      \"args\": [\"mcp\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d"}}, {"chunk_id": "8a2a09bd998f", "text": "Restart Claude Desktop after saving. The Jac tools will appear in the tool picker (hammer icon).", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "8a2a09bd998f"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "4f6de3752296", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Claude Code (CLI)</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "4f6de3752296"}}, {"chunk_id": "d498b2b006ff", "text": "Add to your project's `.mcp.json`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "d498b2b006ff"}}, {"chunk_id": "4fa32db4b1ee", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"jac\": {\n      \"command\": \"jac\",\n      \"args\": [\"mcp\"],\n      \"type\": \"stdio\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "4fa32db4b1ee"}}, {"chunk_id": "ca37b9565817", "text": "Or add it interactively:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "ca37b9565817"}}, {"chunk_id": "e4cdff0284f1", "text": "```bash\nclaude mcp add jac -- jac mcp\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "e4cdff0284f1"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "23a1486f2309", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Cursor</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "23a1486f2309"}}, {"chunk_id": "73418d826aee", "text": "Add to `.cursor/mcp.json` in your project root:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "73418d826aee"}}, {"chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"jac\": {\n      \"command\": \"jac\",\n      \"args\": [\"mcp\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d"}}, {"chunk_id": "00d7a7908df0", "text": "After saving, open Cursor Settings > MCP and verify the server shows a green status indicator.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "00d7a7908df0"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "e216592086f9", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">VS Code with Continue</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "e216592086f9"}}, {"chunk_id": "9e153f61b22d", "text": "Add to your Continue config (`.continue/config.json`):", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "9e153f61b22d"}}, {"chunk_id": "1ba5bf73f0f7", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"jac\",\n      \"command\": \"jac\",\n      \"args\": [\"mcp\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "1ba5bf73f0f7"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "18dd67877b63", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">VS Code with Copilot Chat</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "18dd67877b63"}}, {"chunk_id": "105497fcb3c0", "text": "Add to your VS Code `settings.json`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "105497fcb3c0"}}, {"chunk_id": "f3ec169f6343", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcp\": {\n    \"servers\": {\n      \"jac\": {\n        \"command\": \"jac\",\n        \"args\": [\"mcp\"]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "f3ec169f6343"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "9c0ee168383c", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Windsurf</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "9c0ee168383c"}}, {"chunk_id": "2b3656c99655", "text": "Add to `~/.windsurf/mcp_config.json`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "2b3656c99655"}}, {"chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"jac\": {\n      \"command\": \"jac\",\n      \"args\": [\"mcp\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "9d5ee1cf035d"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "0c40f0f72d97", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Codex</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "0c40f0f72d97"}}, {"chunk_id": "8d54427c8c91", "text": "To add the agent globally:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "8d54427c8c91"}}, {"chunk_id": "3bdf0e55c45c", "text": "```bash\ncodex mcp add jac -- jac mcp\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "3bdf0e55c45c"}}, {"chunk_id": "351a7b8b4dde", "text": "If you prefer a project-local configuration, add `.codex/config.toml`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "351a7b8b4dde"}}, {"chunk_id": "611fa74cbd86", "text": "```toml\n[mcp_servers.jac]\ncommand = \"jac\"\nargs = [\"mcp\"]\ndescription = \"Jac MCP server\"\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "611fa74cbd86"}}, {"chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947", "text": "</details>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "6a2cd75ad947"}}, {"chunk_id": "fb94da6e5b5a", "text": "<details markdown=\"1\">\n<summary markdown=\"1\">Opencode</summary>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "fb94da6e5b5a"}}, {"chunk_id": "2b714c386cec", "text": "Add to `~/.config/opencode/opencode.json`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "2b714c386cec"}}, {"chunk_id": "414faa5e875f", "text": "```json\n{\n  \"mcp\": {\n    \"jac\": {\n      \"type\": \"local\",\n      \"command\": [\n        \"jac\",\n        \"mcp\"\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "reference/mcp.md", "section": "IDE Integration", "chunk_id": "414faa5e875f"}}], "near_dup_candidates": [{"chunk_id_a": "9d5ee1cf035d", "chunk_id_b": "9d5ee1cf035d", "containment": 1.0}, {"chunk_id_a": "9d5ee1cf035d", "chunk_id_b": "5a62d8bd1c3d", "containment": 1.0}]}